The RD-33MK develops 7% higher thrust, is digitally controlled FADEC and smokeless unlike earlier RD-33 engines, has increased afterburner thrust to 9,000 kilograms-force (88,000Â N; 20,000Â lbf) and dry weight 1,145 kilograms (2,524Â lb) compared to the baseline model through modern materials used on the cooled blades, although it retains the same length and maximum diameter.
